28.0,"ebitda_margins":0.37637,"gross_margins":0.45771,"operating_margins":0.22055,"profit_margins":0.17165,"net_income":1693300992.0,"total_cash":3030987008.0,"total_cash_per_share":35.047,"total_debt":4925413888.0,"debt_to_equity":40.655,"enterprise_value":23160813568.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":6.238,"enterprise_to_revenue":2.348,"earnings_growth":-0.123,"shares_outstanding":86576000.0,"float_shares":36935535.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.59259,"held_pct_institutions":0.0143099995,"beta":0.805,"fifty_two_week_high":411.9,"fifty_two_week_low":222.0,"fifty_day_average":276.6,"two_hundred_day_avg":318.204,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":747.475,"all_time_low":17.75,"long_business_summary":"Sanghvi Movers Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a crane rental company in India. It operates through Crane Hiring and Ancillary Services; Wind EPC; and Project EPC segment. The Crane Hiring and Other Ancillary Services segment includes crane rental services, including mobilization and demobilization. The Wind EPC segment includes logistics, intercarting, and installation and commissioning of wind turbine components. The Project EPC segment provides complete lifting and rigging for all heavy lifts, foundation preparation alignment, execution and planning of completion of heavy lifts. It also operates a fleet of medium to large-size hydraulic truck mounted telescopic and lattice boom cranes, as well as hydraulic and crawler cranes. In addition, the company offers equipment, including crawler mounted cranes with lattice boom and truck mounted cranes with telescopic boom. Further, it generates wind and solar power. The company serves construction, power, oil and gas, heavy engineering, infrastructure, renewable wind energy, steel, cement, fertilizers, petrochemical and refinery, and metro railway industries. Sanghvi Movers Limited was incorporated in 1989 and is headquartered in Pune, India."}}